# Example: schedule generated-asset GC on Lightsail (or any VPS).
# (This file is documentation; not executed by the app.)
#
# Prereqs:
#   - App root is the cwd for Node (same directory as server.js, package.json, saves/, data/).
#   - Set on the SERVER (not in git): GENERATED_ASSET_TTL_DAYS=30 in .env or WL_ENV_FILE.
#   - scripts/gc-generated-assets.js loads ../.env and WL_ENV_FILE automatically.
#
# First run (dry-run, inspect log):
#   cd /path/to/airwave-empire && GENERATED_ASSET_GC_DRY_RUN=1 npm run gc:generated-assets
#
# Then install cron (weekly Sunday 04:00 server local time). Replace APP_ROOT and node path if needed:
#
#   crontab -e
#
# Add one line (uncommented):
#
# 0 4 * * 0 cd /home/admin/airwave-empire && /usr/bin/npm run gc:generated-assets >> /home/admin/logs/wl-gc-generated-assets.log 2>&1
#
# Or call node directly (no npm):
#
# 0 4 * * 0 cd /home/admin/airwave-empire && /usr/bin/node scripts/gc-generated-assets.js >> /home/admin/logs/wl-gc-generated-assets.log 2>&1
#
# mkdir -p ~/logs  if the log path does not exist.
#
# Env overrides for one-off tests:
#   GENERATED_ASSET_TTL_DAYS=30 GENERATED_ASSET_MIN_AGE_DAYS=7 npm run gc:generated-assets
